need to modify.\nDo NOT re-read files that are unrelated to the current step.\n\nStep 7: Frontend: NotificationPanel dark-mode fix and AI component polish\n{\n  \"id\": \"step-7\",\n  \"title\": \"Frontend: NotificationPanel dark-mode fix and AI component polish\",\n  \"description\": \"Fix remaining issues in notification and AI components.\\n\\n8a — NotificationPanel MEDIUM priority bg:\\nThe bg-neutral-100 dark-mode violation in NotificationPanel.tsx was already included in Step 1's sweep. Verify it was fixed. Additionally, check if any notification fields render raw UUIDs. Looking at the NotificationResponse interface, it has title/body/priority/referenceId fields — referenceId is not rendered in the UI (only used for navigation), and title/body are human-readable strings from the backend. No UUID display issue exists here, so no additional changes needed.\\n\\n8b — InsightPanel empty state:\\nIn frontend/src/components/ai/InsightPanel.tsx, the PersonalInsightPanel returns null when insights are empty and the TeamInsightPanel already renders 'No AI insights available for this period.' for empty state. Verify these are adequate. If PersonalInsightPanel returning null causes the parent CollapsibleSection to show an empty body, add a brief 'No insights available' message instead of returning null.\\n\\n8c — SemanticSearchInput context-aware suggested questions:\\nIn frontend/src/components/ai/SemanticSearchInput.tsx, the component does NOT have a 'mode' prop — it has teamId and userId props. The suggested questions are hardcoded and team-oriented. Make them context-aware by checking: if only userId is provided (no teamId), show personal-oriented questions (e.g. 'What did I commit to last week?'). If teamId is provided, keep the current team-oriented questions. Use the existing props to determine context — do NOT add a new 'mode' prop.\\n\\n8d — AiCommitComposer RCDO picker search:\\nIn frontend/src/components/ai/AiCommitComposer.tsx, the RCDO tree picker in Phase 2